from test: 13 The oxide film on deformed steel surface was characterized by X-ray Photoelectron Spectroscopy (XPS, Thermo VG Thetaprobe). The 301 LN steel oxide layer composition was analyzed using a two-layer oxide film model that consisted of an iron oxide (Fe2O3) outer layer and a chromium oxide (Cr2O3) interlayer.30 The notch area contained the residual stress due to previous yielding and the location without the stress (i.e. outside the notch area) were analyzed.
from Soup: 13 The oxide film on deformed steel surface was characterized by X-ray Photoelectron Spectroscopy (XPS, Thermo VG Thetaprobe). The 301 LN steel oxide layer composition was analyzed using a two-layer oxide film model that consisted of an iron oxide (Fe 2 O 3 ) outer layer and a chromium oxide (Cr 2 O 3 ) interlayer. 30 The notch area contained the residual stress due to previous yielding and the location without the stress (i.e. outside the notch area) were analyzed.
