from test: 14 The influence of plastic deformation on surface topography and roughness was studied by Atomic Force Microscopy (AFM, Bruker nanoscope multimode 8) using the tapping mode (cantilever frequency of 354.83 kHz). The probe (RTESP MPP-11100) showed a typical tip curvature between 5 and 10 nm.
