from test: 24 The sample was unloaded and LEIS was monitored during exposure in the electrolyte. After 12 h of exposure, the OCP increased by 40 mV to reach −0.34 V/SHE and the local capacitance decreased from 3.4 to 2.5 μF/cm2. Thus, defects in the oxide film repair and in absence of loading the surface can partially re-passivate. The LEIS data in electrolyte are in line with SKP measurements in air (Figure 4A). The potential of the notch area increased and the capacitance decreased after unloading. LEIS and SKP show that the pre-strained carbon steel surface was not stable. XPS measurements conducted a month after straining showed formation of mixed oxide-hydroxide film (Figure 4B).
from Soup: 24 The sample was unloaded and LEIS was monitored during exposure in the electrolyte. After 12 h of exposure, the OCP increased by 40 mV to reach −0.34 V/SHE and the local capacitance decreased from 3.4 to 2.5 μF/cm 2 . Thus, defects in the oxide film repair and in absence of loading the surface can partially re-passivate. The LEIS data in electrolyte are in line with SKP measurements in air ( Figure 4A ). The potential of the notch area increased and the capacitance decreased after unloading. LEIS and SKP show that the pre-strained carbon steel surface was not stable. XPS measurements conducted a month after straining showed formation of mixed oxide-hydroxide film ( Figure 4B ).
