from test: 28 It was assumed31–34 that the formation of dislocations can change the potential drop across the metal/air interface due to variation in the atomic density and accordingly to the interfacial dipole moment (Eq. 1), resulting in a decrease of the ewf at locations of peaks at the rough surface. On the other hand, semiconducting oxide film covered the steel surface. Variation of the atomic density can differently change the surface states in the oxide and ewf.35 Thus, the effect of the surface roughness due to plastic deformation on the potential had to be studied.
