from test: 29 The surface topography was measured for previously strained to 10% elongation carbon steel sample inside and outside of the notch in rectangles of 740 × 440 μm2. A 4-fold average roughness increase from 110 nm to 466 nm due to plastic strain was found, whereas it reached a 7-fold factor (from 92 nm to 690 nm) for stainless steel sample under the same experimental conditions.
