from test: 31 Similar experiments were performed for carbon steel for which the smooth surface showed only an increase of 10 mV of the Volta potential when compared to rough surface. Thus, the effect of the roughness on the potential was much lower compared with effect of the yielding. It is probable that the difference in Volta potentials (Figure 9) is related to residual stress that originates from the grinding.16,36 On the other hand, measurements of capacitance showed that rougher steel surface may lead to higher disordering of the surface oxide, which can also change the electronic properties of the film.37
