from test: 34 The LEIS was applied using the same setup. The measurements of the capacitance were performed in situ during elastic deformation in the range 0–125 MPa in borate electrolyte. The LEIS data show that stress increased the capacitance at the center of the notch from 2.3 to 2.4 10−6 F/cm2 (data are not shown). Thus, elastic tensile strain shows only minor influence on the properties of the steel surface.
